## Architecture

**Backend** — 4 REST endpoints in `todo-app/server.js`:
- `GET /todos` — fetch all todos
- `POST /todos` — create todo
- `PATCH /todos/:id` — update todo (title or completed)
- `DELETE /todos/:id` — delete todo

**Database schema** (`todo-app/prisma/schema.prisma`):
```prisma
model Todo {
  id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  title     String
  completed Boolean  @default(false)
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
}
```

**Frontend** — single page at `todo-frontend/app/page.js`, client component using React hooks.

---

## Code Style Rules

- **Backend**: Keep it simple — async/await handlers, no extra middleware or abstraction layers
- **Backend**: Use Prisma for all DB access — no raw SQL
- **Frontend**: Tailwind CSS is available — use it for styling
- **Auth**: No auth currently — will be added soon

## Things to Avoid
- Don't over-engineer the Express API
- Don't add features not explicitly requested